This PR hopefully addresses https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/issues/10568
Also addresses a need I have with `vscode.diff` to have the same control (for GitLens)

@jrieken This is a first shot at this -- please let me know what you think. I added it as options so that it could be expanded later to allow for other editor options (but didn't want to go there at this stage).

This pr is for using Monaco-editor with vscode-textmate. I use the `setTokensProvider` api for this, but while now the `setTokensProvider` can only accept string tokens, and actually in monaco there is a api called `_toBinaryTokens` to transform the string tokens into Uint32Array, while this api can only accept scopes as a string not a string array which is given from `JsGrammar.tokenizeLine`. So I changed the api for `setTokensProvider` and make it accept a `tokenizeLine2` function to use the Uint32Array tokens directly without `_toBinaryTokens`. The way to do what I want is below:

```js
// get themes from vscode extensions
import { Registry, StackElement } from 'vscode-textmate';
const registry = new Registry();
registry.setTheme({ name: 'Dark+ (default dark)', settings: (DarkTheme.tokenColors.concat(DarkThemePlus.tokenColors)) });
const JsGrammar = registry.loadGrammarFromPathSync('./JavaScript.tmLanguage.json'));
const jsConfig = require('./javascript-language-configuration.json');
languages.register({
  id: 'javascript',
  extensions: ['.js', '.jsx'],
});
languages.setLanguageConfiguration('javascript', jsConfig);
languages.setTokensProvider('javascript', {
  getInitialState: () => {
    return StackElement.NULL;
  },
  tokenize2: (line, state) => {
    const rule = JsGrammar.tokenizeLine2(line, state);
    const ruleStack = rule.ruleStack;
    return {
      tokens: rule.tokens,
      endState: ruleStack,
    };
  },
});
```

